{
  "id": "10113",
  "key": "GG-110",
  "fields": {
    "summary": "Design Sequential Migration Workflow with Error Handling",
    "description": {
      "type": "doc",
      "version": 1,
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Use case:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "As a "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Migration Manager",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", I want to "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "design a sequential migration workflow with error handling",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", so that "
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "the Jira Cloud to Azure DevOps migration can proceed smoothly and any errors can be identified, logged, and addressed promptly",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "strong"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Acceptance criteria:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "GIVEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the Jira Cloud migration process is initiated,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "WHEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the workflow starts,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AND",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " an error occurs during any stage of the migration,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "THEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the system should log the error and halt the migration process at that stage."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "GIVEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " an error has been logged,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "WHEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " a user inspects the logs,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "AND",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " identifies the cause of the error,"
            },
            {
              "type": "hardBreak"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "THEN",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "em"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " the system should provide guidance on how to address the specific error without compromising security."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "rule"
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Technical notes:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The sequential migration workflow should utilize a checkpoint system to ensure that each stage of the migration is completed successfully before proceeding to the next stage. This involves implementing logging and error handling mechanisms at critical points in the process. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In case of an error, the system should immediately stop further execution, log details of the error, and provide clear instructions for troubleshooting or resolving the specific issue. The logs should be accessible only to authorized personnel and never expose sensitive information. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Additionally, it's important to implement mechanisms to resume the migration from the point of failure once the error has been resolved, ensuring that no data is lost or corrupted during this process."
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
